  "text": "Brown et al [CITATION_1] analyzed 4,568 patients who received biologic valves for aortic valve replacement over 15 years and reported a significant incidence of early thrombosis of porcine aortic bioprostheses requiring reoperation: 1.26% for the Biocor valve, 0.37% for the Mosaic valve, and 0.84% for the Hancock valve. They found no cases of thrombosis for the pericardial valve (5,923 patient-years) or the stentless valve (172 patient-years).",
